               <msContents>
                  <summary>Recto contains the right half of a letter in which the sender asks the addressee about his opinion concerning a 'good day' ('and -give me- your opinion, may God strenghten you, concerning the good day'). The verso contains only traces of letters in part of 1 line.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Recto (parallel to fibres) contains 3 lines and has a small blank margin on the right side.</note>
                     <note type="general">Verso (perpendicular to fibres) contains 1 line.</note>
